        <div class="col-md-8 blog-post">
          <div class="col-md-12 blog-post">
            <h2>I am new to JavaScript Templating</h2>
            <p class="text-justify">I am new to JavaScript Templating...</p>
            <p class="text-justify">We strongly recommened you to start with our <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/express-secure-handlebars">integrated Context Parser</a> with Handlebars on Express framework</p>
          </div><!-- blog-post -->

          <div class="col-md-12 blog-post">
            <h2>I am using the Handlebars in client side</h2>
            <p class="text-justify">I am using the Handlebars in client side...</p>
            <p class="text-justify">You can integrate our Context Parser with Handlebars by precompiling the original template files with our <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/secure-handlebars">secure-handlebars</a> and registering the required <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/secure-handlebars-helpers">secure XSS output filters</a> as handlebars' helpers at the client side.</p>
          </div><!-- blog-post -->

          <div class="col-md-12 blog-post">
            <h2>I am using the Express/Handlebars framework</h2>
            <p class="text-justify">I am using the Express/Handlebars framework...</p>
            <p class="text-justify">You can integrate the Context Parser with Handlebars on Express framework at server side with our <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/express-secure-handlebars">express-secure-handlebars</a> npm package.</p>
          </div><!-- blog-post -->

          <div class="col-md-12 blog-post">
            <h2>I want to apply XSS Filters manually</h2>
            <p class="text-justify">I want to apply XSS Filters manually</p>
            <p class="text-justify">You can start with this article to understand how our APIs being designed for our <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/xss-filters">XSS Filters</a>!</p>
          </div>

          <div class="col-md-12 blog-post">
            <h2>more...</h2>
            <p class="text-justify">If you want to have support on other templating engines, please request through <a href="https://github.com/yahoo/context-parser/issues">github issues</a>.</p>
          </div><!-- blog-post -->
